author: satyabrata das
text:
Hello everybody 
I am a son of a Army personal , Who serve 25 year for our country.
After retirement my father wish to build a house as every person.
And we complete our house in 2012 . But unfortunately we build our house in a  place where no house is present which is nearly 500m from a village and close to the state high way. only four to five tribal families are near to us . Then we go to electric office belongs to our region and ask every thing for a new connection .
But the replay from the JE is very  odd and poor . He told that there is no certain kind of government policy   for a single house and indirectly he ask for money at that time my father is with empty pocket every thing is gone to build the house.  so we return home with a empty hand   and after that we tell details to our  gram sarpanch , as we are belongs to a different political party we got a more sad result then the JE  and after that we try too much for a electricity connection but no one can help ................
Till now we have no electricity connection my father bought emergency light and recharge it in near by village .........so we all know the problem when power goes out for 10 min.... but my family suffer from 2012 to till now more then 6 year.....
Now not only us but nearly seven family  staying their still now there is no power...... 
If any one read my message .........kindly help..

reply.author: abhijeetm29
reply.text:
No place in India can boast of 24x7 electricity as of now- blackouts, even though less, are still a reality of India. Some places have it more, some less. 
Your vantage position is more privileged than it is the norm in India. In USA, it would be a general position of most of the population. What poor quality shithole of life exists in India as a norm, is an exception in USA.

What USA lacks in poor Public transport (For majority of country though, the key cities in East ans west coast have P.T. which is better than that of India). Same goes for other safety and status of women indicators. Women are groped and harassed- yes. But not dominated, raped, mutilated and killed as is the case in India.

Finally, you should quit thinking that abroad == USA. There are countries far superior to USA in terms of quality of life. I stay in Europe and here, USA appears like a third world. I can't even imagine what folks think about India here. India is 200 years behind West EU.

reply.author: abhijeetm29
reply.text: I forgot to add that what USA lacks in poor P.t. makes up for it in better quality traffic infrastructure- freeways for instance.
